sourcesContent:
const Ques=
    [
        {subject:"COA",
        question:"what is full form of COA",
        option1:"computer of architect",
        option2:"computer organization art",
        option3:"computer organization and architecture",
        option4:"none of above",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:"What is computer organization?",
        option1:"structure and behaviour of a computer system as observed by the user",
        option2:"structure of a computer system as observed by the developer",
        option3:"structure and behaviour of a computer system as observed by the developer",
        option4:"All of the mentioned",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:"Which of the following is a type of computer architecture?",
        option1:"Microarchitecture",
        option2:"Harvard Architecture",
        option3:"Von-Neumann Architecture",
        option4:"All of the mentioned",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:" Which of the following is a type of architecture used in the computers nowadays?",
        option1:"Microarchitecture",
        option2:" Harvard Architecture",
        option3:"Von-Neumann Architecture",
        option4:"System Design",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:"Which of the following is the subcategories of computer architecture?",
        option1:"Microarchitecture",
        option2:"Instruction set architecture",
        option3:" Systems design",
        option4:"All of the mentioned",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:" Which of the architecture is power efficient?",
        option1:"RISC",
        option2:"ISA",
        option3:"IANA",
        option4:"CISC",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:"What does CSA stands for?",
        option1:"Computer Service Architecture",
        option2:"Computer Speed Addition",
        option3:"Carry Save Addition",
        option4:"None of the mentioned",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:" If an exception is raised and the succeeding instructions are executed completely, then the processor is said to have ______",
        option1:"Generation word",
        option2:"Exception handling",
        option3:"Imprecise exceptions",
        option4:"None of the mentioned",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:" To reduce the memory access time we generally make use of ______",
        option1:" SDRAM’s",
        option2:"Heaps",
        option3:"Cache’s",
        option4:"Higher capacity RAM’s",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"COA",
        question:" The IA-32 system follows which of the following design?",
        option1:"CISC",
        option2:"SIMD",
        option3:"RISC",
        option4:"none of above mentioned",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"What is an operating system?",
            option1:"interface between the hardware and application programs",
            option2:"collection of programs that manages hardware resources",
            option3:"system service provider to the application programs",
            option4:"all of the mentioned",
            answer:"option4"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"What is the main function of the command interpreter?",
            option1:"to provide the interface between the API and application program",
            option2:" to handle the files in the operating system",
            option3:"to get and execute the next user-specified command",
            option4:"none of the mentioned",
            answer:"option3"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:" In Operating Systems, which of the following is/are CPU scheduling algorithms?",
            option1:" Priority",
            option2:" Round Robin",
            option3:"Shortest Job First",
            option4:"All of the mentioned",
            answer:"option4"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"To access the services of the operating system, the interface is provided by the ___________",
            option1:"Library",
            option2:"System calls",
            option3:" Assembly instructions",
            option4:"API",
            answer:"option2"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"CPU scheduling is the basis of ___________",
            option1:"multiprogramming operating systems",
            option2:"larger memory sized systems",
            option3:" multiprocessor systems",
            option4:" none of the mentioned",
            answer:"option1"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"Which one of the following is not true?",
            option1:"kernel remains in the memory during the entire computer session",
            option2:"kernel is made of various modules which can not be loaded in running operating system",
            option3:"kernel is the first part of the operating system to load into memory during booting",
            option4:" kernel is the program that constitutes the central core of the operating system",
            answer:"option2"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:" Which one of the following errors will be handle by the operating system?",
            option1:"lack of paper in printer",
            option2:"connection failure in the network",
            option3:"power failure",
            option4:" all of the mentioned",
            answer:"option4"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"Where is the operating system placed in the memory?",
            option1:"either low or high memory (depending on the location of interrupt vector)",
            option2:" in the low memory",
            option3:" in the high memory",
            option4:"none of the mentioned",
            answer:"option1"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:"If a process fails, most operating system write the error information to a ______",
            option1:"new file",
            option2:"another running process",
            option3:" log file",
            option4:"none of the mentioned",
            answer:"option3"
        },
        {
            subject:"OS",
            question:" Which one of the following is not a real time operating system?",
            option1:" RTLinux",
            option2:"palm OS",
            option3:"QNX",
            option4:"Vx Works",
            answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"What is a computer network?",
        option1:"A device used to display information on a computer screen",
        option2:"A collection of interconnected computers and devices that can communicate and share resources",
        option3:"A type of software used to create documents and presentations",
        option4:"The physical casing that protects a computer’s internal components",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"What is internet?",
        option1:"A network of interconnected local area networks",
        option2:"A collection of unrelated computers",
        option3:" Interconnection of wide area networks",
        option4:"A single network",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"Which of the following is an example of Bluetooth?",
        option1:" wide area network",
        option2:" virtual private network",
        option3:"local area network",
        option4:"personal area network",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"Which of the following computer networks is built on the top of another network?",
        option1:"overlay network",
        option2:"prime network",
        option3:"prior network",
        option4:"chief network",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"What is the full form of OSI?",
        option1:"optical service implementation",
        option2:"open service Internet",
        option3:"open system interconnection",
        option4:"operating system interface",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:" When a collection of various computers appears as a single coherent system to its clients, what is this called?",
        option1:" mail system",
        option2:"networking system",
        option3:"computer network",
        option4:"distributed system",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"How many layers are there in the ISO OSI reference model?",
        option1:"7",
        option2:"6",
        option3:"5",
        option4:"4",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"What are nodes in a computer network?",
        option1:"the computer that routes the data",
        option2:" the computer that terminates the data",
        option3:"the computer that originates the data",
        option4:" all of the mentioned",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"Which one of the following is not a function of network layer?",
        option1:"congestion control",
        option2:"error control",
        option3:"routing",
        option4:"inner netwowrking",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"CN",
        question:"How is a single channel shared by multiple signals in a computer network?",
        option1:"multiplexing",
        option2:"phase modulation",
        option3:"analog modulation",
        option4:"digital modulation",
        answer:"option1"
        },

        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:" What is a data structure?",
        option1:" A programming language",
        option2:"A collection of algorithms",
        option3:"A way to store and organize data",
        option4:" A type of computer hardware",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"What are the disadvantages of arrays?",
        option1:"Index value of an array can be negative",
        option2:"Elements are sequentially accessed",
        option3:"Data structure like queue or stack cannot be implemented",
        option4:"There are chances of wastage of memory space if elements inserted in an array are lesser than the allocated size",
        answer:"option4"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:" Which data structure is used for implementing recursion?",
        option1:"stack",
        option2:"queue",
        option3:"Array",
        option4:"List",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"The data structure required to check whether an expression contains a balanced parenthesis is?",
        option1:"Queue",
        option2:"Stack",
        option3:"Tree",
        option4:"Array",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:" Which of the following is not the application of stack?",
        option1:"Data Transfer between two asynchronous process",
        option2:"Compiler Syntax Analyzer",
        option3:"Tracking of local variables at run time",
        option4:"A parentheses balancing program",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:" Which data structure is needed to convert infix notation to postfix notation?",
        option1:"Tree",
        option2:"Branch",
        option3:"Stack",
        option4:"Queue",
        answer:"option3"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"What is the value of the postfix expression 6 3 2 4 + – *?",
        option1:"74",
        option2:"-18",
        option3:"22",
        option4:"40",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"What data structure would you mostly likely see in non recursive implementation of a recursive algorithm?",
        option1:"Stack",
        option2:"LinkedList",
        option3:"Tree",
        option4:"Queue",
        answer:"option1"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"Which of the following statement(s) about stack data structure is/are NOT correct?",
        option1:" Top of the Stack always contain the new node",
        option2:"Stack is the FIFO data structure",
        option3:"Null link is present in the last node at the bottom of the stack",
        option4:"Linked List are used for implementing Stacks",
        answer:"option2"
        },
        {
        subject:"DSA",
        question:"The data structure required for Breadth First Traversal on a graph is?",
        option1:"Array",
        option2:"Stack",
        option3:"Tree",
        option4:"Queue",
        answer:"option4"
        },
    ]
;
        export default Ques;
